comments.text: Bit inaccurate because Foden has been playing much deeper as left center mid for the majority of this season and has been top. comments.text:
People always make it sound like Foden fell out of the sky in 2023 and suddenly had a word class season. He was good before that, too, you know. 
There's a reason Foden, at the age of 18, started important PL matches in the title race against Liverpool in 18/19 and scored match winners while Cole Palmer couldn't break through until he left age 21. 
Just look at the treble season (year before his PFA season). He was _incredible..._ until a foot injury followed up by an appendectomy sidelined him for a while after which he couldn't break through into the best XI of that season anymore because it was set. 
Still brilliantly assisted the fourth against Madrid minutes after coming on and was one of City's best players in the UCL Final after coming on for KDB

comments.author: @Zxcvbnmq527
comments.text: Liverpool fan here. I watched full match yesterday since our game was over and man i had goosebumps all over. Chelsea what a team. Even after the red card they didn't give up. They weren't bogged down and reece james what a player man he bossed that midfield. I was thinking what would the result would if Caceido didn't get the red card. Cucurela defended very well i thought yellow card will hold him back but he was not afraid to go and make those challenges. Overall i saw a team with grit, passion and determination. And man that chalobah celebration was something else lifted the whole team up. And the more crazy thing was after ten men down they were still looking for equalizer. There was an instance where there were 3 players waiting to counter attack while arsenal was taking corner. I was like these guys are crazy they are leaving arsenal players in box knowing how good they're on set pieces trusting their other players while waiting to pounce on counter attack. This team is special

comments.author: @smacken11
comments.text: The analysts didn't point out a few important facts.  Vancouver's loss to Dallas on decision day was with 10 men on a questionable straight red at the beginning of the game.  A VAR review initiated in Arlington Texas overturned a yellow that was given by the referee.  One call helped Dallas squeak into the playoffs, gave San Diego the western conference and home field advantage, and Miami home field advantage in Cup final.   Vancouver's last loss on the road 4 months ago playing with 10 men in San Jose. Tim Ford's phantom second yellow was overturned by MLS after the game.  Vancouver's close victory over LAFC was with 10 and then 9 men against all odds.  They lost badly in Concacaf champions final after playing 5 games in 2 weeks.  MLS wouldn't reschedule a mid week game going into a Concacaf final in another country.   This is a hardened group of warriors who just dominated every game they got to play with a full team on a level playing field.
